Sentencas: Among all the samples, (PB)0.95FN has the lowest polarization resistance (Rp).

Sentencas: At 800 degrees C, compared with primary PBFN, the cathode Rp of (PB)0.95FN is reduced from 0.109 Omega cm 2 to 0.063 Omega cm 2 in air, whereas the anode Rp is decreased from 0.3808 Omega cm 2 to 0.3109 Omega cm 2 in H 2 .

Sentencas: In addition, an electrolyte-supported single cell with (PB)0.95FN symmetrical electrodes achieves a maximum peak power density at 800 degrees C, which is enhanced by 14.67 % compared with that of PBFN.
